I'm meeting the owner.

251
00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:11.160
I'm impressed! You humiliated
those Ministry bastards.

252
00:32:11.400 --> 00:32:13.600
I didn't think anybody could.

253
00:32:14.760 --> 00:32:17.920
You didn't think; yet. you testified.

254
00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:22.160
We needed medicines
and nobody did anything.

255
00:32:24.760 --> 00:32:27.040
I wouldn't do it again.

256
00:32:28.120 --> 00:32:30.480
Why? Any regrets?

257
00:32:35.960 --> 00:32:37.760
I'll show you something.

258
00:32:47.200 --> 00:32:49.720
That's what
my warehouse looks like now!

259
00:32:49.920 --> 00:32:52.800
- What happened?
- Revenge happened.

260
00:32:53.400 --> 00:32:58.400
Unfortunately. on me.
I don't get any shipping anymore.

261
00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:02.800
What if I could help you...
to fill the shelves?

262
00:33:03.720 --> 00:33:08.520
- But with what?
- The medicine we fought for.

263
00:33:08.920 --> 00:33:13.400
- I could get you some.
- You could? How?

264
00:33:13.760 --> 00:33:15.120
I can't tell you.

265
00:33:17.240 --> 00:33:19.160
I can get you an alternative.

266
00:33:21.240 --> 00:33:27.080
Same substance. same packaging.
The only difference is the price.

267
00:33:33.320 --> 00:33:35.360
You want to sell fakes to me?

268
00:33:38.800 --> 00:33:41.360
Think about it this way...

269
00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:47.960
Patients get drugs they need.
we get money. nobody gets hurt.

270
00:33:48.960 --> 00:33:50.120
It's a win-win!

271
00:33:53.400 --> 00:33:57.640
What about patents. certificates.
documentation? It's a set up!

272
00:33:59.360 --> 00:34:03.520
Fine. Think about it.
You've got my number.

273
00:34:03.920 --> 00:34:07.360
20 %! And guarantees.

274
00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:14.160
I guarantee it's the same drug.

275
00:34:16.280 --> 00:34:18.520
- And I can give you 10 %.
- 20!

276
00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:22.560
I'll risk the most!
Take care of the paper work!

277
00:34:22.800 --> 00:34:24.040
15 %.

278
00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:37.160
We'll be in touch.

279
00:34:50.400 --> 00:34:51.840
Come in!

280
00:34:54.280 --> 00:34:57.960
Hello!
What brings you to me. Mr. Piotr?

281
00:35:01.320 --> 00:35:03.320
He's so beautiful!

282
00:35:05.080 --> 00:35:06.840
Come to Mama!

283
00:35:07.320 --> 00:35:11.000
He's so sweet! Beautiful!

284
00:35:12.880 --> 00:35:15.040
Looks just like my Milo!

285
00:35:16.120 --> 00:35:18.760
- What's your name?
- Drops.

286
00:35:19.240 --> 00:35:22.320
But you could.
of course. name him yourself.

287
00:35:24.920 --> 00:35:27.880
Why did you bring him?

288
00:35:30.040 --> 00:35:33.040
I just wanted to make you happy.

289
00:35:33.240 --> 00:35:37.840
I know how much
you suffered after Milo passed.

290
00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:43.200
I can't accept any gratuities!

291
00:35:44.800 --> 00:35:47.880
It's not a gratuity. doctor.
He's your new friend.

292
00:35:48.360 --> 00:35:52.400
I can't stand when a woman is sad.

293
00:35:53.640 --> 00:35:55.360
You're so beautiful!

294
00:35:56.160 --> 00:35:57.920
Fine! You bought me!

295
00:35:58.960 --> 00:36:00.440
How can I help you?

296
00:36:01.800 --> 00:36:06.920
Actually. I'm the one
who could help our Health Service.

297
00:36:08.560 --> 00:36:09.920
How?

298
00:36:12.800 --> 00:36:15.040
Anticoagulants.

299
00:36:16.880 --> 00:36:22.280
- You know the problem.
- Sure! Everybody's talking about it.

300
00:36:22.480 --> 00:36:26.720
- but nobody can find them.
- I can.

301
00:36:27.640 --> 00:36:32.320
- I could bring you any amount.
- Do it!

302
00:36:32.880 --> 00:36:35.200
You don't need me to do it.

303
00:36:36.160 --> 00:36:41.760
Problem is. I'm looking for
an alternative distribution net.

304
00:36:43.240 --> 00:36:49.320
Come. honey!
Let's get out to the balcony!

305
00:36:50.200 --> 00:36:52.120
Come here!

306
00:36:57.760 --> 00:37:01.800
You want me to sell drugs?

307
00:37:03.400 --> 00:37:04.800
Not at all. doctor!

308
00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:17.920
It's a gross oversimplification.
Your Doctor's Board would do it.

309
00:37:18.800 --> 00:37:23.080
You know a doctor's office
is not a drugstore. we can't.

310
00:37:24.640 --> 00:37:27.440
You'd do it for your patients. doctor.

311
00:37:34.440 --> 00:37:35.640
An invitation.

312
00:37:40.680 --> 00:37:44.520
For a course on new methods
of treating thrombosis.

313
00:37:45.440 --> 00:37:46.800
It'll take a week.

314
00:37:48.280 --> 00:37:50.160
It's in Dominican Republic.

315
00:37:54.720 --> 00:37:58.920
We should help people.
I'll talk to my colleagues.

316
00:38:00.440 --> 00:38:04.440
You could be taking part
in such courses on regular basis.

317
00:38:09.320 --> 00:38:10.480
Come to me!

318
00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:22.240
- Hi!
- Hello!

319
00:38:23.600 --> 00:38:26.720
- How's it going?
- Fine.

320
00:38:27.200 --> 00:38:30.920
- It smells nice.
- We'll have sausage for supper.

321
00:38:37.840 --> 00:38:40.000
- I need to talk to you.
- Talk.

322
00:38:41.360 --> 00:38:44.400
I need to transport
some pills to Poland.

323
00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:48.680
I took care of everything.
I just need your transport route.

324
00:38:54.400 --> 00:38:56.080
It's not for you!

325
00:38:59.600 --> 00:39:05.440
Seriously?! You've been to slammer
and you want to tell me what I can do?

326
00:39:06.960 --> 00:39:09.040
I'm still your father.

327
00:39:15.360 --> 00:39:18.280
- You don't want to help me. don't!
- Piotr!

328
00:39:24.040 --> 00:39:29.960
- I just want to warn you...
- I don't need it! I can do it myself.

329
00:39:44.440 --> 00:39:46.000
Want some?

330
00:39:54.200 --> 00:39:55.600
Finally!

331
00:41:14.120 --> 00:41:16.200
- Hi. Piotr!
- What do you want?!

332
00:41:16.600 --> 00:41:18.280
Take your time peeing!

333
00:41:20.160 --> 00:41:21.440
Pee!

334
00:41:22.720 --> 00:41:25.320
Then
I'll tell you what we're gonna do!

335
00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:07.640
- Have you seen my phone?
- I haven't.

336
00:42:13.840 --> 00:42:16.200
Want to take a look? I'm finished.

337
00:42:28.120 --> 00:42:31.600
- If you don't like any of them...
- I hate them all!

338
00:42:32.440 --> 00:42:34.680
You need to cancel the job.

339
00:42:35.080 --> 00:42:36.360
What?!

340
00:42:36.880 --> 00:42:39.720
- You can't...
- Do I express myself clearly?

341
00:42:40.640 --> 00:42:42.480
You can't work for them.

342
00:42:44.080 --> 00:42:45.560
I love you.

343
00:42:55.640 --> 00:42:57.400
Drink to me!

344
00:42:57.840 --> 00:43:00.000
What the fuck are we doing here?

345
00:43:00.800 --> 00:43:04.200
I heard Lolek's mom
is dancing on the pole!

346
00:43:05.680 --> 00:43:07.640
Carrying her sister!

347
00:43:08.240 --> 00:43:09.520
Fuck you!

348
00:43:10.440 --> 00:43:13.080
Kid!
You'll get laid. you'll feel better!

349
00:43:13.800 --> 00:43:16.520
But with whom? His mom or her sister?

350
00:43:20.880 --> 00:43:23.760
Don't you worry. kid.
We're just hazing you.

351
00:43:25.440 --> 00:43:27.600
It was me who invited you here.

352
00:43:27.720 --> 00:43:30.200
- Great!
- Where's Mr. Andrzej?

353
00:43:31.840 --> 00:43:33.880
Getting to know his family.

354
00:43:35.040 --> 00:43:38.120
We've got the new king!
Leyer the Lawyer!

355
00:43:42.680 --> 00:43:47.800
Gentlemen!
Are you ready to make big money?

356
00:43:49.120 --> 00:43:51.560
On Lolek's mom?

357
00:44:15.280 --> 00:44:17.120
It's Lolek's mom's jubilee!

358
00:44:25.720 --> 00:44:27.480
Where's the sister at?

359
00:45:31.360 --> 00:45:33.000
You don't belong here.

360
00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:36.040
What?

361
00:45:37.240 --> 00:45:39.040
You don't belong here.

362
00:45:45.520 --> 00:45:46.760
This helps.

363
00:45:48.120 --> 00:45:50.600
And nobody was asking for my opinion.

364
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:53.600
Was it supposed
to be a modeling career?

365
00:45:54.720 --> 00:45:56.960
Money. photos. catwalks in Milan.

366
00:45:58.600 --> 00:46:00.600
And they took your passport?

367
00:46:01.160 --> 00:46:03.120
It was different in my case.

368
00:46:03.680 --> 00:46:06.840
Did you know you'll end up here
and become a...

369
00:46:07.880 --> 00:46:11.760
- hostess?
- They found me on this App.

370
00:46:12.640 --> 00:46:15.640
- Instagram. You know it?
- Come one...

371
00:46:16.400 --> 00:46:19.920
There was supposed to be
a party on this big. fancy yacht.

372
00:46:21.160 --> 00:46:23.160
And of course a lot of money.

373
00:46:27.000 --> 00:46:29.360
And now you're here with me.

374
00:46:32.560 --> 00:46:36.920
I'm here because they didn't want
to cut off a good looking girl.

375
00:46:40.880 --> 00:46:42.400
So. what's your story?

376
00:46:43.120 --> 00:46:45.320
What about you. tell me!

377
00:46:45.840 --> 00:46:47.520
Do you like what you do?

378
00:46:48.400 --> 00:46:49.560
Yeah...

379
00:46:51.480 --> 00:46:53.000
I fucking love it!

380
00:46:55.680 --> 00:46:57.080
Come on!

381
00:47:09.600 --> 00:47:11.200
How are you two?

382
00:47:13.040 --> 00:47:14.440
Us?

383
00:47:15.160 --> 00:47:18.360
Well. you and Piotr.

384
00:47:19.560 --> 00:47:21.320
You know what I mean.

385
00:47:29.160 --> 00:47:31.360
He's got a lot on his plate.

386
00:47:32.560 --> 00:47:35.560
He won in court.
then his brother died.

387
00:47:36.080 --> 00:47:37.400
You came.

388
00:47:38.640 --> 00:47:41.080
He just needs to relax.

389
00:47:42.800 --> 00:47:45.680
He won't be able to relax anymore.

390
00:47:51.280 --> 00:47:53.040
What is it that you want?

391
00:47:54.520 --> 00:47:58.960
Piotr is a great lawyer.
We've got kids. we've got plans.

392
00:47:59.120 --> 00:48:02.080
We love each other.
It's gonna be OK again.

393
00:48:06.960 --> 00:48:12.480
He's gonna change.
You don't get it yet. but he will.

394
00:48:13.160 --> 00:48:17.480
It's good you know everything!
Your prison friends told you?

395
00:48:19.960 --> 00:48:23.480
You might actually be right.

396
00:48:25.400 --> 00:48:27.240
I've been through it all.

397
00:48:29.240 --> 00:48:33.640
I spent my boys' childhood in prison.

398
00:48:34.880 --> 00:48:36.880
I didn't get to meet you.

399
00:48:38.280 --> 00:48:40.600
I didn't see him graduate.

400
00:48:42.280 --> 00:48:47.200
I didn't go to your wedding.
didn't welcome my grandkids.

401
00:48:48.760 --> 00:48:51.040
Ela took care of everything.

402
00:48:52.360 --> 00:48:55.320
And then I didn't go to her funeral.

403
00:48:56.480 --> 00:48:58.080
They wouldn't let me.

404
00:49:00.760 --> 00:49:03.840
You want your kids
to have such a life?

405
00:49:07.720 --> 00:49:11.640
Piotr is different from you!
Completely!

406
00:49:14.480 --> 00:49:16.000
Wait a minute!

407
00:49:17.720 --> 00:49:19.040
Did you hear that?

408
00:49:47.480 --> 00:49:48.960
Bring some water!

409
00:50:31.320 --> 00:50:33.360
Dance with me. honey!

410
00:50:36.320 --> 00:50:38.040
No. thank you!

411
00:50:42.840 --> 00:50:44.320
I'm sad...

412
00:50:57.120 --> 00:50:59.200
Is that how you leave a party?

413
00:50:59.560 --> 00:51:01.520
I need to go. See you!

414
00:51:02.520 --> 00:51:05.360
If it wasn't for you. I'd be in jail!

415
00:51:08.320 --> 00:51:11.000
- Thank you. brother.
- Sure.

416
00:51:12.520 --> 00:51:14.360
One of us is an informer.

417
00:51:18.160 --> 00:51:20.760
That's why I had Frajda follow you.

418
00:51:26.760 --> 00:51:29.560
Now I know it's not you. right?

419
00:51:32.160 --> 00:51:33.800
She's quite elegant.

420
00:51:38.080 --> 00:51:39.680
I know.

421
00:52:04.240 --> 00:52:05.920
It needs thorough airing.

422
00:52:06.440 --> 00:52:07.880
Fuck it. Piotr!

423
00:52:08.840 --> 00:52:11.160
- You didn't see anybody?
- I didn't!

424
00:52:11.320 --> 00:52:16.400
- Maybe you heard something.
- I didn't. officer. honestly!

425
00:52:17.640 --> 00:52:22.280
- And you suspect nobody?
- Officer! You know

426
00:52:22.560 --> 00:52:25.360
I had a 15 year-long vacation!

427
00:52:26.400 --> 00:52:28.040
Yeah. I know that.

428
00:52:29.960 --> 00:52:33.400
- You don't need a doctor?
- No! I'm fine!

429
00:52:33.920 --> 00:52:37.240
- And the boys?
- No. thank you.

430
00:52:39.200 --> 00:52:41.480
I get it. That's all for now.

431
00:52:41.960 --> 00:52:44.760
- Thank you. officer.
- Thank you. bye.

432
00:52:45.440 --> 00:52:47.600
Fine. boys! Let's go to bed.

433
00:52:48.320 --> 00:52:52.200
Boys! Remember the song
we sang yesterday?

434
00:54:04.240 --> 00:54:05.960
Big smile. Grandpa!

435
00:54:17.640 --> 00:54:19.800
- Look who's here!
- Good evening!

436
00:54:20.040 --> 00:54:22.680
- A bit late!
- I was working. Dad.

437
00:54:23.120 --> 00:54:25.320
- Dad?
- Let it go.

438
00:54:25.400 --> 00:54:26.720
Working!

439
00:54:30.520 --> 00:54:32.560
- Good evening!
- Evening!

440
00:54:33.560 --> 00:54:35.240
The last one!

441
00:54:37.440 --> 00:54:39.120
It's great. thank you!

442
00:54:39.840 --> 00:54:41.480
Bye!

443
00:54:42.240 --> 00:54:45.040
- See you at school!
- You're leaving?

444
00:54:45.360 --> 00:54:47.080
My mom is waiting.

445
00:54:52.200 --> 00:54:54.960
Happy Birthday!
I'm sorry. Love you!

446
00:54:55.200 --> 00:54:58.040
I left some cake for you.

447
00:55:12.560 --> 00:55:15.040
- Thank you!
- That's what you wanted?

448
00:55:18.760 --> 00:55:22.600
They are great!
Aunt Ewa bought me a helmet.

449
00:55:25.560 --> 00:55:26.800
It's nice.

450
00:55:27.240 --> 00:55:29.920
Let's go for a smoke and I'll be gone.

451
00:55:30.240 --> 00:55:32.080
It's so nice of you.

452
00:55:34.760 --> 00:55:37.760
Try them on!
Mom will let you skate in here.

453
00:55:38.560 --> 00:55:39.840
Sure thing!

454
00:55:41.440 --> 00:55:42.720
Delicious cake.

455
00:55:43.600 --> 00:55:45.240
I'll be right back.

456
00:55:50.560 --> 00:55:52.280
Are they the right size?

457
00:55:56.400 --> 00:55:57.880
Aunt Ewa?! For real?

458
00:56:01.760 --> 00:56:04.360
- I had to get to you.
- On her birthday?

459
00:56:07.720 --> 00:56:09.520
Did you find out anything?

460
00:56:11.240 --> 00:56:12.920
Head is growing back.

461
00:56:14.520 --> 00:56:17.960
- Ambitious Chechen?
- It's not Mamuka.

462
00:56:19.440 --> 00:56:21.400
- Who then?
- Piotr Leyer.

463
00:56:23.880 --> 00:56:25.080
The lawyer on TV?

464
00:56:26.400 --> 00:56:30.000
I don't believe it!
He was the white sheep.

465
00:56:30.840 --> 00:56:32.920
He want's to deal medicines.

466
00:56:33.920 --> 00:56:35.120
How?

467
00:56:36.000 --> 00:56:37.720
I don't know yet.

468
00:56:40.480 --> 00:56:44.320
I take it
you're gonna see it to the end.

469
00:56:49.760 --> 00:56:51.920
It's my daughter's birthday!

470
00:56:58.760 --> 00:57:00.280
How much longer?!

471
00:57:01.400 --> 00:57:04.280
- She'll forget you.
- Can't you understand?

472
00:57:04.440 --> 00:57:07.720
- It's her birthday!
- I didn't know Ewa would come!

473
00:57:07.960 --> 00:57:10.160
- We had to meet!
- Today?!

474
00:57:10.560 --> 00:57:11.800
It's not that easy!

475
00:57:11.920 --> 00:57:14.800
It's so easy!
Either you change it or I will.

476
00:57:47.320 --> 00:57:48.600
I'm listening.

477
00:57:50.120 --> 00:57:53.160
I'd like to report
an assault and battery.

478
00:57:59.640 --> 00:58:01.480
I have it all on camera.

479
